{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"73f6cb8e-2e41-4dc5-823a-f03fc32bb66b","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp`:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.5.0\" />\n   ```\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Or upgrade to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"1.0.2\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.2\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test executable directly (MTP produces a self-contained test host).\n\n> **Note:** If you stay on xUnit v2, `xunit.runner.mtp` is a bridge adapter. If you can upgrade to xUnit v3, that's the recommended long-term path as it has native MTP support. The v3 upgrade may require minor code changes (e.g., namespace updates, `Assert` API tweaks).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8515d1e1-83a5-40c1-8188-984363cb9d5e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":440},"id":"424cef0b-e4ef-4947-9b85-4c20be041f0d","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:41:43.092Z","parentId":"e18a74ee-7b8d-4390-8ad4-8bf5cf8c2966"}
